hedt:Motor-seizure a hed:HedTag ;
    rdfs:label "Motor-seizure" ;
    rdfs:comment "Involves musculature in any form. The motor event could consist of an increase (positive) or decrease (negative) in muscle contraction to produce a movement. Definition from ILAE 2017 Classification of Seizure Types Expanded Version" ;
    hed:hasHedParent hedt:Seizure-classification .

hedt:Movement-artifact a hed:HedTag ;
    rdfs:label "Movement-artifact" ;
    rdfs:comment "Example for EEG: Large amplitude artifact, with irregular morphology (usually resembling a slow-wave or a wave with complex morphology) seen in one or several channels, due to movement. If the causing movement is repetitive, the artifact might resemble a rhythmic EEG activity." ;
    heda:suggestedTag hedt:Artifact-significance-to-recording,
        hedt:Brain-laterality,
        hedt:Brain-region,
        hedt:Multifocal-finding,
        hedt:Sensors ;
    hed:hasHedParent hedt:Biological-artifact .

hedt:Mu-rhythm a hed:HedTag ;
    rdfs:label "Mu-rhythm" ;
    rdfs:comment "EEG rhythm at 7-11 Hz composed of arch-shaped waves occurring over the central or centro-parietal regions of the scalp during wakefulness. Amplitudes varies but is mostly below 50 microV. Blocked or attenuated most clearly by contralateral movement, thought of movement, readiness to move or tactile stimulation." ;
    heda:suggestedTag hedt:Brain-laterality,
        hedt:Brain-region,
        hedt:Finding-frequency,
        hedt:Finding-significance-to-recording,
        hedt:Sensors ;
    hed:hasHedParent hedt:Background-activity .

