hedt:Sleep-walking a hed:HedTag ;
    rdfs:label "Sleep-walking" ;
    rdfs:comment "Episodes characterized by ambulation during sleep; the patient is difficult to arouse during an episode, and is usually amnesic following the episode. Episodes usually occur in the first third of the night during slow wave sleep. Polysomnographic recordings demonstrate 2 abnormalities during the first sleep cycle: frequent, brief, non-behavioral EEG-defined arousals prior to the somnambulistic episode and abnormally low gamma (0.75-2.0 Hz) EEG power on spectral analysis, correlating with high-voltage (hyper-synchronic gamma) waves lasting 10 to 15 s occurring just prior to the movement. This is followed by stage I NREM sleep, and there is no evidence of complete awakening." ;
    heda:suggestedTag hedt:Clinical-EEG-temporal-relationship,
        hedt:Episode-awareness,
        hedt:Episode-consciousness,
        hedt:Episode-event-count,
        hedt:Episode-phase,
        hedt:Episode-postictal-phase,
        hedt:Episode-prodrome,
        hedt:Episode-tongue-biting,
        hedt:Finding-significance-to-recording,
        hedt:State-episode-start ;
    hed:hasHedParent hedt:Sleep-related-episode .

hedt:Slow-alpha-variant-rhythm a hed:HedTag ;
    rdfs:label "Slow-alpha-variant-rhythm" ;
    rdfs:comment "Characteristic rhythms mostly at 4-5 Hz, recorded most prominently over the posterior regions of the head. Generally alternate, or are intermixed, with alpha rhythm to which they often are harmonically related. Amplitude varies but is frequently close to 50 micro V. Blocked or attenuated by attention, especially visual, and mental effort. Comment: slow alpha variant rhythms should be distinguished from posterior slow waves characteristic of children and adolescents and occasionally seen in young adults." ;
    heda:suggestedTag hedt:Appearance-mode,
        hedt:Brain-laterality,
        hedt:Brain-region,
        hedt:Discharge-pattern,
        hedt:Sensors ;
    hed:hasHedParent hedt:Physiologic-pattern .

hedt:Slow-eye-movement-artifact a hed:HedTag ;
    rdfs:label "Slow-eye-movement-artifact" ;
    rdfs:comment "Slow, rolling eye-movements, seen during drowsiness." ;
    heda:suggestedTag hedt:Artifact-significance-to-recording,
        hedt:Brain-laterality,
        hedt:Brain-region,
        hedt:Multifocal-finding,
        hedt:Sensors ;
    hed:hasHedParent hedt:Biological-artifact .

hedt:Slow-fused-transient a hed:HedTag ;
    rdfs:label "Slow-fused-transient" ;
    rdfs:comment "A posterior slow-wave preceded by a sharp-contoured potential that blends together with the ensuing slow wave, in children." ;
    heda:suggestedTag hedt:Appearance-mode,
        hedt:Brain-laterality,
        hedt:Brain-region,
        hedt:Discharge-pattern,
        hedt:Sensors ;
    hed:hasHedParent hedt:Uncertain-significant-pattern .

